english_title: Flames of Passion: On the Edge of Glory
content_vision: Getaway. I need to get away from this relationship to freedom. Tomorrow I'll be gone.
structure_suggestion_description: Beautiful song about breaking up and getting your long deserved freedom.
text:
Intro:
cruisin' in my red hellcat, feelin' fast and free,
but you treat me like i'm back in love again, ain't no guarantee.

Verse 1:
i've been through the fire, got scars to prove it,
but you can't expect me to be fine, i'll put up a fight.
you know she's got that fire too, man, she could blow like a torch,
with her by my side, i can take on anything, of course.
it takes more than fame, it takes me,
i'll never die, i'll reign eternally, you'll see.
you let us down like that, now we must rise,
together we can be heroes, no need to hide,

Pre-Chorus 1:
i'll keep you safe, hidden in my treasure chest,
like a queen, bitch i'm madonna, let's begin this quest.

Chorus 1:
feels like the weight of the world on me, so hard to breathe,
but i'll keep dancing on the edge of glory, fighting to achieve.
gotta take that hella chopper to the top,
'cause the stars are callin', we gotta pray for this world non- stop.

Verse 2:
you got my heart racing, what is that scent in the air,
what cologne do you wear, it's got me feeling like i just don't care.
as an og, she be spittin' fire,
that's why they call her the 50 cent sire.
sipping on my holy wine, it's divine,
aida! aida! heavenly waters flow down the line.
take off your mask, let's close this case,
it won't be the last time, baby, no trace

Pre-Chorus 2:
all eyes on us, everyone around can see,
she knows i'm the one, can't stop calling my phone, so free

Chorus 2:
get your shit bust, ain't no time for pretending
you won't believe what you see, the truth you've been amending.
got no time for petty drama and games,
and as an old soul, i'll still fuck them haters properly, no shame.

Bridge:
i ain't afraid of living, i'll take the risk,
you know what you do to me, damn girl, can't resist.
are you where you ought to be, on top of your game?
they know the name, never gonna forget it, fame's the same.

Outro:
i finalize you, make you mine, no matter what you see
i'll never let go, you'll always be with me.

Theme melody:
when times get tough, keep your faith in god above,
let him lead the way, show us the meaning of love,

Instrumental:
yeah, i'm living my life, cyeah that's for sure,
and this lady got me feeling all kinds of things, she could blow me away like a torch.

what's in your arsenal, what you got ready to fire,

you let us down like that, now we must rise,

they may not know our struggles, but they'll know our fame,

dimming my light, i won't let him control me,

take it, girl, make it yours, it's all for you
and then tell me all your deepest desires, what you wanna do.
no matter what goes down, we'll stick together,
so confused, wanna ask you, how we'll come out better?

Chorus 3:
who's not afraid to sing, to help us all understand
love her back, back, take a stand.
even if i die, we can never be apart,
our love's too strong, nothing can break our hearts.

all i see is green, chasing money like a fiend,
but she's just trying to feel grown, living up to society's dream.
i've been through the fire, got scars to prove it,
but you can't expect me to be fine, i'll put up a fight.

i'll make it on my own, ain't gotta kneel,

Intro:
no license, no insurance, calling me out,
i gotta better get low, take the safe route.

Verse 1:
so la da di da di, my rhymes are critical
you look just like him, my flow is identical.
you think you know me, act like ya know,
but sometimes i surprise, bringin' the rice and makin' it slow.
they weren't bad, but they weren't good,
just mediocre, misunderstood.
hey potna, my homie, what's good with you?
and what was that you said to me, what's your view?

Pre-Chorus 1:
i've arrived, my reign is here,
and don't act like you didn't know, or is it fear?

Chorus 1:
your girl looking like kimmy gibbler, all loud and wild,
feels like just yesterday i was a young child.
now i'm sittin' back, smokin' gas in my joint,
reminiscing 'bout the days when we didn't have to appoint.

Verse 2:
i'm feeling so old in this game,
but still staying true on crip, nigga.
yo, it's your boy sky blu, comin' through with the flow,
or you could meet at my house, kick back and chill, yo,
no need for the drama, no time for the fame,
'cause that's just straight up lame.
fuck the handle, ain't no need to lock the door,
and all you do is talk that talk, but what for?

Pre-Chorus 2:
or you could meet me at my place, where we can be free,
residue on my helmut lang, let's get high and see what we can be.

Chorus 2:
trapped in a cycle of pain and despair,
in this baby universe, do we even care?
does it quench our thirst, or leave us bare?
everything got a purple tint, feelin' blurry

Bridge:
they just want blood and to get the thrill,
now i'm a dead man, they're out to fulfill.
it all began with a little crush
but now she's grown, she's intelligent and flush.

Outro:
you taught me to never take shit, i got no time for it,
patience? nah, that's something i'll never commit.

Theme melody:
gotta stay chill, frigid like ice,
ignore all the crap you advertise, not worth my time.

Intro:
there's a reason why they call me a bad bitch,
i ride through life like a funky flute, never hitch.

Verse 1:
i can't forget the past, gotta go back to the down note,
no matter where i go, i know where i came from, resilient and bold.
as i fade away, morphing into the mist around me,
you been a naughty girl, can't resist your lust, can't flee.
no stain on my soul, just trying to find my clementine,
forgive me for running, i was scared of what we could be.
sipping on that patron got me faded,
no patience left, just death, enlightenment has evaded.

Pre-Chorus 1:
people always tryna hold me back,
but i can't lose my focus, gotta stack that paper, yeah that's a fact.

Chorus 1:
my flow so smooth, it's like i'm rolling lah,
these lyrical vocals leave haters in awe.
rolling with my ninja, taking risks,
but who knows, i might just get lucky with this.

Verse 2:
before you make a move, better ask god above,
'cause messing with me ain't no game of love.
got you feeling trapped, right in the back,
trusss, just listen and say!
lost in a haze with a purple tint,
so confused, i just wanna ask, do you have a hint?
my dreams, they feel so far away,
and my jewelry, it's so icy it'll put you in a daze.

Pre-Chorus 2:
i count it all with my eyes closed, it's all the same,
you can still play this game, but don't forget my name.

Chorus 2:
back up, fool, i ain't playing, let's not trip
just smokin' dips, while they smokin' dick.
no need to front, no need to trip,
'cause keeping it real ain't lame, it's just legit.

Bridge:
let me disappear, sip on that purple drank
in my zone, nothing else to think.
i'm in my zone, feeling the flow,
worship me like i'm your god, and pick up all the cash, let it grow.

Outro:
bitch, bitch, always at my throat,
that's how it goes when you're hustling for your oats.

Theme melody:
sippin' on some coors light, got my mind in a trance,
another plan in the works, never taking a chance.

Instrumental:
thought i had it all figured out,
but look up in the cup, reality hits with a shout,

Intro:
that lbc swag, we straight servin' heat for ya fam,
while you out here getting played for your cash, got scammed.

Verse 1:
she may not be from my hood, but she's still got that fire,
can't even explain how much i miss you, my desire.
in this life, can't even tell december from june,
but keep watching out, you never know what's comin' for you soon.
bullets flying out through the crowd, but i don't stop and flee,
they turning into the mist, floating around me.
if we blew up, hit it big, go platinum and gold
but right now, i just wanna dig this music and let it unfold.

Pre-Chorus 1:
if you ever cross the line, disrespectin',
better believe i'll defend what's mine, no question.

Chorus 1:
your girl lookin' like a 90s sitcom,
and these dudes actin' soft, they must be made of cotton.
even when they mess up, people are still human,
gotta make it right, and show compassion.

Verse 2:
you say you gettin' rich, but i can see it's all a lie,
and all that political talk, it's just a waste of my time.
i'll be the judge to finalize you,
but you can still play this game, make it through.
i wanna give you a heads up, let you know,
'cause back then wasn't too long ago.
i'm hanging on by a thread, down to my last breath,
but still i'm intelligent, my mind's always racing with thoughts that could lead to my death.

Pre-Chorus 2:
we ain't normal, call us crazy, we don't give a damn,
got bezels on bezels, shining bright, living wild and free, that's the plan.

Chorus 2:
death keeps shaking, trying to bring me down
but i can't sleep with a man who wants to douse my crown.
we never slow down, keep moving ahead,
and in the end, we were always inseparable, like thread.

Bridge:
in this life i feel half asleep,
and my enemies are everywhere, cuttin' deep.
seeking a way out, can't stay in this space,
and that bothers me, feel like i'm losing the race.

Outro:
she be fakin' on a real one, ain't got no time for that fake
expand my mind, riches i can't take.

Instrumental:
been around the world, traveled with pac
now i'm back, million dollar stacks, yeah.

Verse 1:
before i go, gotta let you know one more thing,
sweet joni from saskatoon, love that girl, she my queen.
all the lies you spew, all the things you feign,
he looks more like a fake, frigid in vain.
she's a gangsta through and through
nothing fazes her, no matter what people do.

Pre-Chorus 1:
it takes me higher, to a place i never thought i'd reach,
got her mind sprinting like a track meet, making my dreams into reality, no need to preach.

Chorus 1:
stackin' up that cash, we workin' with some paper,
we workin' with some paper, and he gonna give you all his love, no caper.
before i go, gotta let you know one more thing,
sweet joni from saskatoon, love that girl, she my queen.

Verse 2:
and 10s in my pocket, not afraid to spend it all,
violent prone atonement, rising up and standing tall.
all of em like to shoot, can't you see the trend?
when will it end, burying our friends?
got my head up high, everything seems so clear,
ain't no one gonna stop me, traversing my turf with no fear,
i speak the truth, my word is like king james of the street,
let my light shine bright, for all the world to see.

Pre-Chorus 2:
fuck these brothers always talking shit,
but you know he's got it, that real grit.

Chorus 2:
no contracts, we don't play, only real talk is what my dogs say.
in the dim candlelight, i reminisce about the past,
but then i snap back to reality, return to the down note, just gotta make it last.
my art is my escape, that's why i do music,

Bridge:
livin that long beach life with that fresh swag,
but these streets be like a jigsaw puzzle, gotta watch your back.
i was drawn to her mind, captivated by her brains,
now i'm regretting wasting all my time on you, it's a shame.

Outro:
ain't no contract, something you just can't say
rockin' those fresh jordans on your feet, feeling okay.

Theme melody:
they gotta grind hard just to make ends meet
but i don't need to hustle, success comes so sweet.

Instrumental:
i'm cruisin' in my ride like the funky flute,
smooth as gravy, ain't no one can refute.

Verse 1:
we ain't got time for hatin' or holdin' grudges,
just gotta fuck them bitches properly and handle our business,
cut up everywhere, but we'll still rise above this.
my dream is bigger than me, i can't look away,
even when you got me feeling some type of way.
i can't lose focus, gotta stay on track,
'cause what you do to me, girl, it's more than just a heart attack.
she's a beautiful sinner, i can't resist her charms,

Pre-Chorus 1:
girl you got me feeling so divine,
you're one of a kind, everyone can see, you shine.

Chorus 1:
i may act fearless, but deep down it's not true,
you can't expect me to be fine when life's throwing everything at me,
but i'll keep living never scared, with 50 cent yeah that's my creed.
you can't escape, the lies they tell,

Verse 2:
been in the game since i was just a child,
but still ain't got no time for fancy drinks, no mai tais,
yeah, i'm older now, but my flow still wild, that's a given, cyeah.
tired of all these games we play, i just want to be free,
to be myself, to love until kingdom come, to just be.
representing for the crew, you know how we do
brothers keeper, that's right, we loyal like nino.
we gotta break em off somethin',

Pre-Chorus 2:
they be hatin' on me, but i'm still elegant,
just tryna make moves, stayin' intelligent.

Chorus 2:
got my eye on that dime, gotta make her mine
she got a fine ass, watch her get low on the whine.
been waking up to love songs, on my tippy toes,
do i really want to jump into another relationship, who knows.

Bridge:
every time i see her, i die a little inside,
but hey, she can't deny i've got her mind caught in a track meet, heehee!
we all crying for the things we can't change
and ladies, don't let them hold you back, don't be tame.
